<ol>
    <h2> Sheet Pan Italian Sausage Heros with Honey Mustard</h2>
    <img src="hoagie.jfif" alt="hoagie" width="500px"><br>
    <p> Things you will need</p>
        <li> mild Italian sausage (turkey, chicken or pork) normally contains 5 sausages</li>
        <li>green bell pepper, cored, 3/4" sliced</li>
        <li> red bell pepper, cored, 3/4" sliced</li>
        <li>½ tsp salt</li> 
        <li>1 tbsp olive oil</li>
        <li>hoagie rolls, toasted</li>
    <p>Method of cooking</p>
        <li>Heat oven to 425°F..</li>
        <li>place the bell peppers and onion on a rimmed baking sheet. Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with salt, toss to coat.</li>
        <li>Nestle the sausages in between the veggies and roast for 30 minutes.</li>
        <li>In a small bowl mix the mayonnaise, whole grain mustard, honey and soy sauce.</li>
        <li>Remove the sausage and veggies from the oven and toss with the sauce or drizzle on top once in the hoagie roll.</li>
        <li>Serve sausage and veggies on toasted hoagie rolls smothered in the sauce.</li>
        <li>Lastly enjoy</li>

